HEADWORD: Dermis
<hw>Der"mis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Derm</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The deep sensitive layer
of the skin beneath the scarfskin or epidermis; -- called also
<altname>true skin</altname>, <altname>derm</altname>,
<altname>derma</altname>, <altname>corium</altname>,
<altname>cutis</altname>, and <altname>enderon</altname>. See
<er>Skin</er>, and <xex>Illust.</xex> in Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dermobranchiata</ent>⟦br⟧
